                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p rend=\"align(right)\"><date>Friday 8th of Adar (March</date>),</p>\n            <p rend=\"align(right)\"><date>1860</date>.</p>\n            <p>To my friend, etc.</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">Dear Friend,</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(2)\">I am much indebted for your<lb/> few lines. The sermon is very well\n                translated.<lb/> It will be noticed I am proud to say it is no<lb/> worse than that\n                of <persName>Einhorn</persName> whose first address<lb/> inclined towards\n                Coverservatism - “and before a<lb/> blind man do not set a stumbling block.”*\n                There-<lb/>fore should be met half-way from the Conservative<lb/> side. That is why\n                I must insist that you print<lb/> my article in German at once, and, at the same\n                time,<lb/> improve it. If I send you the article at the<lb/> same time as the\n                sermon, it is only because they<lb/> belong together. I depend upon it. You see<lb/>\n                to what extent <persName>Wise</persName> takes him under his wing <add>?</add><lb/>\n                Here <persName>Wise</persName> caused a great deal of harm among the Jews<lb/> of\n                all classes. That is why such an answer must<lb/> be made. What is worse,\n                    <persName>Wise</persName> is already <add>blank</add><lb/> That is why you must\n                call this to people's attention.</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">My friend, the deed is more important<lb/> than the doer. If you\n                want to arrange<lb/> for my lecture, speak to the directors,<lb/> but with my honor\n                and the honor of<lb/> the Torah in mind. I am at your</p>\n            <p>* Leviticus</p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3fn1182x/canvas/p1"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
